<br>
What came from MiM was just a bunch of bs, like &quot;how do we know Once was in range&quot; etc etc etc. and it took the people involved, Zayda and Isildr, like 3 weeks to finally say what I already knew, which was basically &quot;Once is our friend&quot;.<br>
<br>
MiM decides themselves who to kill or not kill when the person is a PK.  At the same time, they preach about the &quot;laws of the server&quot;, laws which they disregard however it suits MiM.<br>
<br>
As for myself personally.  If I am faced with an MiM and a PK as my targets, I would first engage the MiM and after my primary enemy was dead, I would switch to the PK.  My reasons for doing so are strategic.  For one thing, I do not fear pks or their pvp ability.  The main weapon of a PK is that they attack people when they do not suspect it, their target is exping or whatever, and thus surprise is the primary tactic they use.  Secondly, I know if I first engage a PK, the MiM target would fully take advantage of that situation and attack me.  I am also not going to call a &quot;time out&quot; if I am fighting a MiM member and a PK runs up, because I know my enemies and they would not do the same.  <br>
<br>
Now if MiM wants to discuss rules of engagement and to agree to break off any and all attacks to first rid a zone of PKs if any appear, then I would discuss and agree to that, however the MiM of today is not a guild like that, their officers do not put forth rules of war or negotiate in civilized manners.  So for now, I treat MiM and PK alike, both enemies and targets, but for me personally I choose my primary target on who I dislike the most, and that will always be MiM.<br>
